6. REVISION AND CONFIGURATION CONTROL
------------------------------------------------------------

- All component IDs tracked in Configuration Management Plan (/00_System_Definition/Configuration_Management_Plan.txt).  
- Extrusion lengths verified against Frame Cut List before fabrication release.  
- 3D printed part revisions logged per Printed Parts Specification.  
- Any dimensional update requires Class B or higher Change Request.  

------------------------------------------------------------
7. DESIGN INTENT
------------------------------------------------------------

This Bill of Materials defines the mechanical component baseline for OBSIDIAN‑8 V3.3 hybrid frame.
It links the structure directly to the Frame Architecture and Printed Parts Specification to ensure:

- Dimensional consistency across fabrication and assembly  
- Traceable mass and geometry for mechanical simulation  
- Controlled material transitions between aluminum and printed components  
- Repeatable modularity for maintenance and upgrades  

